    <note>Huang(2) Zongdan [861] He was the elder cousin of the wives of Xie(1) Zhonggui's [729] father (twice: sororate). Zongdan and Fan(2) Zhongyan [8043] were respectively the fathers of the first and second wives of Xuzhou(c) resident, Yan(4) Chongguo [4112]. The daughter of Li(2) Changling's [974] cousin, Li(2) Changyun [3472], was Chongguo's mother and Changling's son or nephew, Li(2) Yuqing(a) [3553], was the father of Yan(4) Chongguo's third wife. According to Fan Chunren, Chongguo's fathers-in-law were all from famous lineages (xingzu). Fan Chunren, WJ, 14.16b; Fujian TZ, 147.5a; XCB, 72.4a-4b, 99.1b-2a. CBD, 4, 2899.</note>
